&lt;li&gt;Establish yourself as a trusted leader for the team, with working rhythms and clear ownership across the function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Launch at least one new growth channel or partnership initiative that opens up a sustainable traffic or acquisition source.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of the go-to-market for upcoming feature launches and turn it into measurable acquisition or activation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set direction for durable, diversified growth - new acquisition that holds up - not one-off spikes or vanity reach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full marketing strategy for Seobility — all channels, with accountability for results and budget (yearly six-figure PPC spend, freelancers, and project investments).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own product-led and diversified growth: build sustained acquisition sources beyond our Google-organic base, turn feature launches into measurable acquisition and activation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop a team of 2–3 mostly senior marketers — strategic direction, coaching, clear priorities, and planning that keeps delivery on track.&lt;/li&gt;
